        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "TPM (Trusted Platform Module)", "Back": "Hardware chip providing secure cryptographic key storage. Enables organizational hardware integrity checks and protects against firmware-level tampering and unauthorized system modifications and changes."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "HSM (Hardware Security Module)", "Back": "Physical device protecting digital keys for strong authentication. provides highly secure cryptographic processing and prevents key extraction through physical and logical organizational barriers."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Symmetric Encryption Method", "Back": "Encryption using a single shared key for locking and unlocking. it is fast and efficient for processing large organizational information volumes and assets."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Asymmetric Encryption Method", "Back": "Public-key cryptography using linked key pairs. enables secure key exchange and digital signatures, ensuring confidentiality and integrity between various organizational and external parties."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Diffie-Hellman Algorithm", "Back": "Key exchange algorithm for establishing shared secrets over insecure channels. provides the mathematical foundation for many secure organizational communication protocols and encrypted sessions."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "RSA Cryptographic Algorithm", "Back": "Asymmetric encryption based on factoring large prime numbers. provides strong security for data encryption and digital signatures, essential for modern organizational identity systems."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "AES (Advanced Encryption Standard)", "Back": "Global standard for symmetric encryption. uses variable key lengths to provide robust protection for sensitive organizational data at rest across all infrastructure."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Cryptographic Hashing", "Back": "One-way function producing a unique fixed-length output. used to verify organizational data integrity by detecting any changes to the original message or information file."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Data Salting", "Back": "Adding random data to passwords before hashing. prevents rainbow table attacks and ensures identical passwords result in unique hashes within organizational identity systems."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Digital Signature Mechanism", "Back": "Cryptographic tool providing proof of origin and integrity. uses a private key to sign hashes, ensuring organizational senders cannot deny involvement."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "PKI (Public Key Infrastructure)", "Back": "Framework of hardware and software managing digital certificates. enables secure identity verification and encrypted communication across large distributed organizational networks and partners."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "CA (Certificate Authority)", "Back": "Trusted entity issuing and managing digital certificates. verifies certificate holder identities and maintains revocation lists to ensure organizational platform-wide security and integrity."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Defense in Depth Strategy", "Back": "Layered approach using multiple controls to protect assets. ensures that if one barrier fails, others are in place to prevent organizational breaches."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Least Privilege Principle", "Back": "Granting only minimum access needed for functions. limits potential damage from compromised accounts and is a fundamental design requirement for all systems."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Secure Defaults Configuration", "Back": "Pre-configured settings providing maximum protection. requires users to explicitly enable risky features, reducing the likelihood of accidental organizational security vulnerabilities and gaps."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Fail-Safe System Design", "Back": "Principle where systems default to secure states upon failure. prevents unauthorized access or organizational harm when technical components stop functioning correctly."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Economy of Mechanism Principle", "Back": "Design principle favoring simple security mechanisms. smaller codebases are easier to test and verify, reducing the probability of hidden organizational vulnerabilities and errors."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Complete Mediation Requirement", "Back": "Mandatory check for every access request. ensures that organizational security controls cannot be bypassed, even after an initial user authorization was granted."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Open Design Security", "Back": "Security should not rely on secrecy of the mechanism. encourages peer review and robust testing to ensure organizational protections remain effective against adversaries."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Isolation Technique", "Back": "Separating processes or users into distinct environments. prevents a compromise in one area from affecting other parts of the entire organizational system or network."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Ring Protection Architecture", "Back": "Hierarchical CPU architecture isolating the kernel from applications. Ring 0 has highest privileges, preventing user programs from causing organizational system crashes."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Zero Trust Security Model", "Back": "Model assuming no entity is trusted by default. requires continuous verification of every organizational user and device, regardless of their network location."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Privacy by Design Framework", "Back": "Embedding privacy protections into the initial system design. ensures user confidentiality is a core requirement rather than an added organizational software feature."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "SaaS (Software as a Service) Architecture", "Back": "Protections for cloud application environments. relies on strong identity management and encryption to maintain organizational control over data stored in external software."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service) Architecture", "Back": "Protections for cloud infrastructure. requires organizational management of guest systems while the provider secures the underlying physical and virtualization hardware layers."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "PaaS (Platform as a Service) Architecture", "Back": "Protections for cloud platforms. allows organizations to focus on application security while the provider manages and secures the underlying infrastructure components."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "ICS (Industrial Control Systems) Security", "Back": "Systems managing critical infrastructure like power. require specialized measures to protect against physical impacts and ensure constant organizational availability of services."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IoT (Internet of Things) Security", "Back": "Protecting network-connected physical devices. requires robust segmentation and firmware updates to prevent vulnerable organizational items from becoming easy attack entry points."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Microservices Security Design", "Back": "Software design using small, independent services. simplifies security by isolating components, ensuring a breach in one service doesn't compromise the organizational application."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Containerization Isolation", "Back": "Isolating applications within lightweight containers. requires image scanning and runtime monitoring to prevent malware from spreading between different organizational workloads and environments."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Serverless Function Security", "Back": "Protecting event-driven functions in the cloud. requires granular access controls and monitoring of execution environments to safeguard organizational data during processing."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Edge Computing Protection", "Back": "Distributed architecture bringing processing near data sources. requires localized controls to protect organizational info before transmission to central corporate or cloud servers."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Hypervisor Security", "Back": "Controls protecting the virtualization management layer. requires isolation between guest machines and monitoring for attacks attempting to escape virtualized organizational IT environments."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Cryptographic Algorithm Lifecycle", "Back": "Management of encryption from key generation to destruction. ensures that organizational information remains protected throughout its existence using secure and current mathematical methods."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Quantum-Resistant Cryptography", "Back": "Mathematical algorithms designed to resist quantum attacks. provides protection against future powerful computers, ensuring long-term confidentiality for sensitive organizational communication and data."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Key Management Process", "Back": "Techniques protecting and controlling cryptographic keys. includes generation and rotation, ensuring only authorized organizational users can access encrypted and protected information assets."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Brute Force Mitigation", "Back": "Controls preventing trial-and-error credential guessing. includes account lockouts and rate limiting to protect organizational system and data access from automated attacks."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Side-channel Mitigation", "Back": "Defending against physical cryptosystem leaks. uses noise and constant-time algorithms to prevent adversaries from extracting organizational keys through power or timing clues."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Fault Injection Protection", "Back": "Defending hardware against deliberate error induction. aims to prevent organizational systems from entering insecure states that allow unauthorized access or key extraction."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Memory Protection Mechanism", "Back": "Technique preventing processes from accessing unauthorized RAM areas. essential for system stability and preventing malicious code from stealing sensitive organizational information."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "HPC (High-Performance Computing) Security", "Back": "Protections for large-scale data processing systems. focuses on ensuring organizational data integrity and availability while maintaining extreme operational processing and transmission speeds."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Pass-the-Hash Attack", "Back": "Stealing a hashed password to authenticate to systems. allows attackers to gain organizational access without ever knowing the original user's secret cleartext credentials."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Implementation Vulnerability", "Back": "Attack exploiting flaws in how systems are built. targets specific organizational coding or configuration errors rather than theoretical weaknesses in cryptographic algorithms."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Chosen Ciphertext Analysis", "Back": "Cryptanalytic method where adversary decrypts selected data. clues help them deduce organizational keys and break the overall mathematical protection of systems."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Facility Security Design", "Back": "Physical measures protecting organizational buildings. include cameras and barriers designed to prevent unauthorized individuals from reaching sensitive areas and critical hardware assets."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Environmental Hazard Control", "Back": "Maintaining safe conditions for critical hardware. include fire suppression and HVAC to prevent equipment failure and ensure continuous organizational service availability."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Power Redundancy System", "Back": "Using generators and UPS for critical systems. ensures organizational functions remain available and allows for a graceful shutdown if primary utility power fails."},
        {"Topic": "3", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Secure Software Engineering", "Back": "Comprehensive design and implementation of application protections. ensures that all organizational technical components work together to safeguard critical information and systems."},

        # TOPIC 4: COMMUNICATION AND NETWORK SECURITY (60 Terms)
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "OSI (Open System Interconnection) Reference Model", "Back": "Seven-layer framework for network communications. Standardizes how organizational hardware and software interact, from physical connections up to high-level application and user services."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "TCP/IP (Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol) Model", "Back": "Four-layer protocol suite powering global networks. includes Link, Internet, Transport, and Application layers, providing a practical framework for efficient organizational data transmission."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IPsec (Internet Protocol Security)", "Back": "Protocol suite authenticating and encrypting IP packets. provides strong confidentiality and integrity for organizational network traffic, essential for secure VPNs and communication."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "TLS (Transport Layer Security)", "Back": "Protocol providing secure communication over untrusted networks. encrypts data between organizational applications and servers, ensuring privacy for web browsing and digital transmissions."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Segmentation", "Back": "Dividing a network into isolated zones. it is a critical operational control that limits lateral movement of attackers and contains breaches."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "SDN (Software-Defined Networking)", "Back": "Architecture decoupling network control from forwarding. Enables centralized management, allowing security policies to be applied dynamically and consistently across all organizational infrastructure."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "VLAN (Virtual Local Area Network)", "Back": "Logical network segments within a physical switch. it improves organizational security and performance by isolating traffic between different departments on shared hardware."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "VPN (Virtual Private Network)", "Back": "Secure, encrypted tunnel over untrusted networks. Enables organizational users to access internal resources privately, protecting sensitive information from interception and maintaining confidentiality."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "DMZ (Demilitarized Zone)", "Back": "Separate network segment hosting public-facing services. It isolates these systems from sensitive internal organizational networks, reducing risk if an external server compromised."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "CDN (Content Delivery Network)", "Back": "Distributed network of servers delivering content based on location. improves performance and provide protection against DDoS attacks for organizational web services."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "NAC (Network Access Control)", "Back": "System restricting network entry to authorized devices. it ensures that all organizational systems meet protection standards before being allowed to connect."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "WPA3 (Wi-Fi Protected Access 3)", "Back": "Latest Wi-Fi security protocol. Provides stronger encryption and improved protection against brute-force attacks, ensuring secure wireless connectivity for all modern organizational devices."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "DNSSEC (Domain Name System Security Extensions)", "Back": "Security extension for Domain Name Systems. uses digital signatures to verify data integrity and prevent cache poisoning attacks against organizational users."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Microsegmentation", "Back": "Granular network security creating secure zones around workloads. prevents lateral movement of threats within organizational data centers and complex cloud infrastructure environments."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "WAF (Web Application Firewall)", "Back": "Security device protecting applications by filtering HTTP traffic. it prevents attacks like SQL injection and cross-site scripting from reaching organizational software."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "API (Application Programming Interface) Gateway", "Back": "Management tool acting as a single entry point for traffic. enforces security policies, provides rate limiting, and protects underlying organizational services."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "BGP (Border Gateway Protocol) Security", "Back": "Protections for routing protocols connecting autonomous systems. essential for maintaining the overall security and integrity of global organizational internet routing and connectivity."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Zero Trust Network Architecture", "Back": "Security model where no device is trusted by default. requires strict identity verification and least privilege for every connection within organizational infrastructure."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "EDR (Endpoint Detection and Response)", "Back": "Security solution monitoring individual devices for threats. provides advanced detection and automated response to identify and neutralize sophisticated attacks on organizational hardware."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "UTM (Unified Threat Management)", "Back": "Single appliance consolidating multiple security functions like firewalls. simplifies management and provides comprehensive protection for smaller organizational network environments and IT systems."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Switching Fabric Security", "Back": "Design of data forwarding within a LAN. includes techniques like store-and-forward, impacting organizational network speed and the ability to perform security filtering."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Routing Protocol Security", "Back": "Rules for directing traffic between different networks. includes measures to prevent route hijacking and ensure the integrity of organizational network connectivity."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Wireless Access Point Security", "Back": "Measures protecting over-the-air data transmissions. includes encryption and strong authentication to prevent unauthorized access and interception of organizational wireless communications and data."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Cellular Infrastructure Security", "Back": "Protections for mobile data transmissions. requires encryption and strong authentication to safeguard organizational information moving across global 4G and 5G network infrastructures."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Physical Network Segmentation", "Back": "Using separate hardware to isolate network traffic. provides the highest level of security for critical organizational systems by preventing any logical cross-communication."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Logical Network Segmentation", "Back": "Using software methods like VLANs to isolate traffic. flexible and cost-effective method for managing organizational security across shared physical network hardware components."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Traffic Shaping", "Back": "Managing network flow to prioritize critical business services. ensures that essential organizational applications have required bandwidth while maintaining a secure communication environment."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Performance Observability", "Back": "Deep insights into organizational network activity. essential for threat detection and identifying anomalies that could indicate potential security incidents or active system breaches."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Convergence Security", "Back": "Merging different traffic types onto single networks. requires robust organizational security controls to protect diverse data like VoIP from unauthorized access or modification."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Physical Air-Gapping", "Back": "Isolation of secure networks from all other systems. providing absolute protection for highly sensitive organizational data that must never connect to the internet."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Protocol Encapsulation", "Back": "Wrapping data within another protocol for protection. secures organizational information during transmission by hiding its true content from unauthorized observers on the network."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Protocol Analysis", "Back": "Evaluating communication based on protocol standards. identifies organizational vulnerabilities and misconfigurations that could be exploited by attackers to gain unauthorized system access."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Packet Sniffing", "Back": "Capturing and analyzing traffic for troubleshooting. used by organizational administrators for monitoring but also by attackers to steal info from unencrypted communications."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "ARP (Address Resolution Protocol) Spoofing Attack", "Back": "Attack linking a MAC address with a legitimate IP. allows interception or alteration of traffic within the organizational local area network segment."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "DDoS (Distributed Denial of Service) Attack", "Back": "Attack using compromised systems to flood a target. aims to overwhelm organizational resources and make services unavailable to all legitimate business users."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Proxy Server", "Back": "Intermediary between clients and the internet. it hides the user's IP address and provides content filtering for enhanced organizational network security."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "NAT (Network Address Translation) Security", "Back": "Mapping private IPs to one public address. it conserves space and provides basic organizational security by hiding internal network structure from external observers."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Port Scanning", "Back": "Technique used to identify open services on hosts. used for organizational security assessments and by attackers to find potential system entry points."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Banner Grabbing", "Back": "Collecting info from service welcome screens. helps attackers identify organizational software versions to target specific vulnerabilities during an active cyber exploit attempt."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "RADIUS (Remote Authentication Dial-In User Service) Protocol", "Back": "Protocol providing centralized user management. ensures consistent organizational security across multiple access points through standardized authentication and authorization processes and system components."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "TACACS+ (Terminal Access Controller Access-Control System Plus) Security", "Back": "Protocol for centralized network management authentication. provides better security than RADIUS by encrypting entire organizational communication sessions between devices and the server."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "802.1X Access Control", "Back": "IEEE standard for port-based network security. it provides an organizational authentication mechanism for devices connecting to a LAN, ensuring only authorized systems."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "EAP (Extensible Authentication Protocol) Framework", "Back": "Authentication framework for wireless links. supports multiple methods, providing flexibility and strong security for diverse organizational user environments and various IT systems."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network IP Spoofing", "Back": "Attack sending packets with a fake source address. used to hide identity or bypass IP-based organizational access controls and traffic filters."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "TCP SYN Flood Attack", "Back": "DoS attack exploiting the handshake process. adversary sends many requests but never completes connections, overwhelming organizational server resources and making services unavailable."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "ICMP (Internet Control Message Protocol) Flood Attack", "Back": "DoS attack using many ping requests. aims to overwhelm organizational network bandwidth and CPU, making systems unresponsive and causing significant business disruption."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "UDP (User Datagram Protocol) Flood Attack", "Back": "DoS attack sending many UDP packets. the organizational system becomes overwhelmed by the traffic volume and the processing required to handle connection attempts."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Botnet", "Back": "Network of compromised computers under attacker control. used to launch large-scale DDoS attacks and spread malware, threatening the overall security of organizational networks."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "C2 (Command and Control) Security", "Back": "Infrastructure used to manage botnets. securing the network requires identifying and blocking command-and-control traffic to prevent attackers from managing compromised organizational systems."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "NIPS (Network Intrusion Prevention System) Control", "Back": "Proactive measure blocking detected cyber attacks. NIPS tools provide real-time protection by automatically responding to threats before they can cause harm to organizational systems."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Baseline Performance", "Back": "Measure of normal activity and speed. used as a reference point to detect organizational anomalies and security incidents that deviate from behavior."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Forensic Analysis", "Back": "Capture and study of traffic for investigations. helps organizational security teams understand how a breach occurred and identify the actions taken by adversaries."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Vulnerability Management", "Back": "Automated process identifying known network weaknesses. provides a regular check-up of the posture and helps administrators prioritize remediation and patching efforts effectively."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Incident Response", "Back": "The coordinated effort to manage security breaches. network teams play a key role by containing threats and restoring organizational operations as quickly as possible."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Threat Hunting", "Back": "Proactively searching for hidden attackers within networks. uses advanced analysis to identify organizational compromises that have bypassed traditional security controls and mechanisms."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Log Management", "Back": "Collection and storage of activity logs. essential for compliance, auditing, and forensic investigations, providing a detailed record of all organizational network events."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Defensive Strategy", "Back": "Comprehensive plan for protecting communications. combines layering, segmentation, and encryption to safeguard organizational information assets from various evolving and sophisticated cyber threats."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Infrastructure Protection", "Back": "Protecting routers, switches, and cabling. requires systematic tracking and hardening to prevent unauthorized access and tampering with critical organizational digital communication components."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Communications Security Management", "Back": "Discipline of protecting organizational information transmissions. combines various technical and physical controls to maintain confidentiality, integrity, and availability of all network assets."},
        {"Topic": "4", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Transmission Security", "Back": "Protecting data as it moves between systems. requires encryption and secure protocols to prevent unauthorized interception and ensure organizational communication integrity and secrecy."},

        # TOPIC 5: IDENTITY AND ACCESS MANAGEMENT (IAM) (60 Terms)
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Identification", "Back": "Process of a user claiming an identity. involves providing a unique username or ID within the organizational environment to start access."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Authentication", "Back": "Process of verifying a claimed identity. requires providing credentials like passwords or tokens to prove the user is who they claim to be."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Authorization", "Back": "Process of granting or denying access to resources. determined by organizational policy and permissions, ensuring users only reach authorized information and systems."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Accountability", "Back": "Ability to link actions to an individual. achieved through unique IDs and audit logging, ensuring organizational users are responsible for their system interactions."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication)", "Back": "Verification using two or more credential types. significantly increases organizational security by ensuring a single compromised factor does not lead to an information system breach."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Something You Know", "Back": "Credential based on memorized information. includes passwords and PINs, being the most common but also the most vulnerable organizational identity and access management factor."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Something You Have", "Back": "Credential based on physical objects. includes smart cards and hardware tokens used to provide a strong secondary layer of security for organizational verification."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Something You Are", "Back": "Credential based on physical characteristics. includes biometrics like fingerprints, providing high security for sensitive organizational systems while requiring careful privacy management and oversight."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Somewhere You Are", "Back": "Credential based on physical location. uses GPS or IP address to restrict organizational system access to specific geographic areas, enhancing overall security and defense."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Something You Do", "Back": "Credential based on behavioral patterns. includes typing speed or gait, providing continuous verification to ensure the authorized organizational user is still the one performing actions."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "SSO (Single Sign-On)", "Back": "Mechanism allowing one authentication for multiple systems. it reduces password fatigue and improves organizational user experience while simplifying administrative identity management and oversight."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Kerberos Authentication", "Back": "Ticket-based protocol providing SSO. uses a trusted third party to verify organizational identities and provide session keys, ensuring secure communication across untrusted networks."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "SAML (Security Assertion Markup Language)", "Back": "XML-based framework for identity federation. enables secure exchange of authentication and authorization data between different organizational security domains and various web applications and services."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "OAuth Delegation", "Back": "Open standard for access delegation. allows organizational users to grant third-party apps limited access to resources without revealing their secret passwords or other sensitive credentials."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "OpenID Connect Identity", "Back": "Identity layer built on OAuth 2.0. allows organizational clients to verify end-user identity based on authentication performed by a trusted external authorization server and provider."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Federation Framework", "Back": "Linking user identities across different security domains. allows users to access organizational resources in partner systems using their primary internal corporate credentials and identification."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Directory Service System", "Back": "Centralized database for users and resources. Provides a single management point for identities and access rights, enforcing consistent organizational security and protection policies."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "LDAP (Lightweight Directory Access Protocol)", "Back": "Protocol for accessing directory information services. it is the primary method used by modern organizational identity management systems to maintain and query user data."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "RBAC (Role-Based Access Control)", "Back": "Grants permissions based on job function. simplifies organizational management and ensures employees only have the access they need for their specific roles and duties."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "DAC (Discretionary Access Control)", "Back": "Allows resource owners to determine access. provides flexibility but is difficult to manage securely in large organizational information system environments and technical settings."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "MAC (Mandatory Access Control)", "Back": "Restricts access based on security labels. enforced by the system, it is the most secure organizational model for sensitive information environments and critical assets."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "ABAC (Attribute-Based Access Control)", "Back": "Grants access based on user/resource characteristics. provides highly granular organizational control suitable for complex and evolving security requirements and various complex information system environments."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Rule-Based Access Management", "Back": "Grants access based on predefined system rules. enforced by organizational firewalls and routers to control traffic flow and resource usage according to security policies."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Privilege Management Oversight", "Back": "Managing and monitoring administrative access rights. requires extra protection and regular reviews to prevent unauthorized use of high-level organizational system permissions and critical information assets."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Least Privilege", "Back": "Granting only minimum access needed for tasks. reduces organizational attack surface and limits potential damage from compromised accounts or accidental human errors and operational system mistakes."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Need-to-Know", "Back": "Restricting information access to individuals needing it for tasks. fundamental organizational security principle that prevents unnecessary exposure of sensitive data and information assets within systems."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Provisioning", "Back": "Process of creating user accounts and access. must be handled securely to ensure new organizational employees receive only the permissions required for their specific business roles."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Deprovisioning", "Back": "Formal process of removing access when no longer required. critical for preventing orphaned accounts and reducing unauthorized access risks in the organizational digital environment and infrastructure."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Access Certification Review", "Back": "Periodic evaluation of user permissions. ensures access still aligns with roles and identifies unnecessary entitlements for immediate removal from the organizational identity management system."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Orphaned User Account", "Back": "Account remaining active after an employee leaves. poses significant risk as it can be used by adversaries to gain unauthorized organizational system access and sensitive data."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Shadow IT IAM", "Back": "Use of software/hardware without IT approval. creates organizational gaps by bypassing established identity management controls and oversight, leading to potential data security and privacy breaches."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Context-Aware Authentication Control", "Back": "Authentication adapting based on the user's environment. uses location and time to adjust the required verification level for accessing sensitive organizational information assets and systems."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Step-Up Authentication Requirement", "Back": "Requiring extra verification for high-risk actions. ensures sensitive organizational activities receive more security, even if the user is already authenticated to the information system environment."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Continuous Verification Process", "Back": "Ongoing identity checking during a session. uses behavioral factors to ensure the authorized organizational user is still the one performing actions within the protected system environment."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Biometric Error Management", "Back": "Measure of accuracy for characteristics systems. includes FAR and FRR, which must be balanced to ensure effective organizational security and user convenience during identity verification."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "CER (Crossover Error Rate) Metric", "Back": "The point where FAR and FRR are equal. most important metric for evaluating overall organizational biometric system accuracy and performance during identity management and verification."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Password Complexity Policy", "Back": "Rules defining required complexity and rotation frequency. aims to reduce brute-force risks and ensure organizational user credentials remain secure against various cyber threats and adversaries."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Password Manager Tool", "Back": "Tool storing and generating strong credentials. it improves organizational security by encouraging the use of unique and complex passwords for every internal and external application system."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "PAM (Privileged Access Management) System", "Back": "Systems securing administrative accounts. provides extra organizational protection including session recording and just-in-time provisioning to reduce the time high-level credentials are exposed and vulnerable."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Just-In-Time Access Control", "Back": "Granting administrative permissions only when required. reduces the organizational attack surface and limits the risk of credential theft for high-level information system access and administrative control."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "UEBA (User and Entity Behavior Analytics) Monitoring", "Back": "Monitoring activity to detect anomalies. helps identify potential organizational threats like account compromise or malicious insider behavior by identifying deviations from normal patterns within digital systems."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Proofing Verification", "Back": "Verifying real-world identity before granting digital credentials. essential first step in ensuring the overall integrity and trustworthiness of the organizational identity management system and data access."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Governance Strategy", "Back": "Strategic management of user identities. ensures IAM practices align with business goals and comply with mandated organizational and legal data protection requirements and privacy standards and regulations."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Access Certification Process", "Back": "Formal review of user permissions. ensures employees only have currently needed access and identifies potential organizational security risks for immediate remediation and corrective action and oversight efforts."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Entitlement Management Lifecycle", "Back": "Lifecycle management of user access rights. ensures that entitlements are granted and removed consistently and securely across all organizational systems and sensitive and valuable digital information assets."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Role Mining", "Back": "Analyzing activity to identify common access patterns. helps organizations define and refine their RBAC roles, improving the overall efficiency and accuracy of identity management and protection processes."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Delegated Administration Control", "Back": "Assigning administrative tasks to designated groups. it improves organizational efficiency while maintaining strong security controls by reducing the burden on central IT departments and security monitoring teams."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Self-Service Identity Management", "Back": "Allowing users to manage passwords without assistance. improves experience and reduces organizational costs while requiring strong secondary verification to maintain overall system-wide security and data protection."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Digital Identity Management", "Back": "Representation of an individual in computer systems. includes attributes used to authenticate and authorize organizational users for various resources and sensitive information assets and critical business systems."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IDaaS (Identity as a Service) Solution", "Back": "Cloud-based management solution. simplifies deployment and provides scalable identity management for organizations with diverse and evolving IT environments and application needs and various security and compliance requirements."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Lifecycle Management", "Back": "Stages of identity management. includes provisioning and deprovisioning, each requiring specific organizational security controls to ensure constant data protection throughout the entire user account and access cycle."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Access Control Mechanism Enforcement", "Back": "Technical tool enforcing access policies. includes passwords and encryption designed to maintain organizational confidentiality and integrity of all digital resources and information assets and system components."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Authentication Protocol", "Back": "Rules governing identity verification. protocols like SAML provide secure methods for exchanging data across organizational domains and various untrusted network and system environments and infrastructure components."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Authorization Policy", "Back": "Document defining which users reach specific resources. enforced by the system, it ensures access follows organizational security policies and the fundamental and essential principle of least privilege."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "IAM Audit Logging", "Back": "Recording access and security events. provides a detailed record for compliance and forensic investigations, ensuring every organizational user is accountable for their system activities and digital interactions."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity Provider Service", "Back": "Service authenticating users for other systems. essential for identity federation and enabling SSO across diverse organizational and external application environments and various service platforms and information systems."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Service Provider Application", "Back": "Application relying on an IdP for authentication. uses identity data to authorize organizational users for specific resources and information assets within its secure and protected environment."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Federation Trust Relationship", "Back": "Agreement between systems to accept authentication data. foundation for organizational identity federation and enabling secure cross-domain access for authorized users and system components and critical organizational resources."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Attribute-based Authorization", "Back": "Grants access using user/resource characteristics. used in ABAC to make granular organizational decisions based on location, role, and other relevant contextual and technical factors and environmental conditions."},
        {"Topic": "5", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Identity and Access Management Strategy", "Back": "Discipline managing digital identities and resource access. ensures the right people have right access at right time for right reasons across all organizational systems and digital assets."},

        # TOPIC 6: SECURITY ASSESSMENT AND TESTING (60 Terms)
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Assessment Process", "Back": "Systematic evaluation of an organization's protection posture. identifies vulnerabilities and provides actionable recommendations to strengthen the defense of critical information assets and systems and organizational digital infrastructure."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Vulnerability Assessment Cycle", "Back": "Process of identifying and prioritizing known security weaknesses. provides regular check-ups and helps organizational administrators prioritize remediation and patching efforts effectively based on business and technical risk."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Penetration Testing Methodology", "Back": "Authorized simulated attack evaluating security defenses. identifies organizational gaps and tests control effectiveness against real-world adversaries and sophisticated cyber threats and various attack methods and vectors."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Audit Evaluation", "Back": "Formal evaluation of adherence to established standards. provide objective evidence of compliance and identifies areas for improvement to maintain a robust organizational security posture and information protection."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Compliance Scanning Tool", "Back": "Automated checking of systems against protection standards. ensures organizational assets are configured correctly and meet all mandated legal and industry data protection and security requirements and regulations."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Vulnerability Scanner Technology", "Back": "Tool automatically identifying known software weaknesses. provides a comprehensive view of potential organizational security gaps and facilitates the ongoing and essential vulnerability management and remediation and mitigation process."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Scanning Tool", "Back": "Tool identifying active devices and open ports. helps administrators understand the organizational attack surface and find unauthorized or vulnerable network systems and services and various infrastructure components."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Code Review", "Back": "Systematic examination of source code for flaws. identifying vulnerabilities early reduces the risk of releasing insecure organizational applications and protects sensitive information from potential disclosure or unauthorized access."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "SAST (Static Application Security Testing)", "Back": "Examining code for vulnerabilities without execution. provides immediate feedback to developers, identifying common organizational coding errors like injection flaws early in the software development lifecycle process and activities."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "DAST (Dynamic Application Security Testing)", "Back": "Testing running applications for security flaws. identifies issues visible only during execution, such as organizational session management errors and complex application-layer security vulnerabilities and various technical gaps."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Application Fuzz Testing", "Back": "Providing random or invalid data as input. identifies organizational vulnerabilities like crashes and memory leaks that could be exploited by adversaries to compromise systems and information and technical processes."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Misuse Case Testing Strategy", "Back": "Evaluating system response to malicious activities. identifies organizational security gaps and helps design applications that are resilient against common adversary methods and various attack vectors and techniques."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Regression Testing", "Back": "Verifying that security fixes don't break existing features. essential for maintaining the integrity and reliability of organizational applications throughout their entire software development lifecycle and maintenance phases."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Interface Security Testing", "Back": "Evaluating communication security between system components. ensures data is transmitted safely and access policies are enforced across all organizational system and network boundaries and connections and interfaces."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Audit Trail Documentation", "Back": "Chronological record of system and user activities. provides irrefutable evidence for compliance and forensic investigations, ensuring accountability across the entire organizational information technology environment and infrastructure assets."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Log Analysis", "Back": "Systematic review of security logs for threats. automated tools help organizational teams sift through data to spot anomalies and indicators of compromise quickly and effectively and accurately."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Continuous Security Monitoring", "Back": "Ongoing evaluation of the organizational security posture. provides real-time visibility into control effectiveness and helps detect threats and compliance issues as they arise within various protected organizational systems."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Performance Metric", "Back": "Quantitative measure of protection performance. used to track control effectiveness and provide a data-driven basis for making informed organizational security and business management and strategy decisions."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security KPI (Key Performance Indicator)", "Back": "Key Performance Indicator for security success. help organizations monitor progress toward goals and ensure that protective efforts are adding maximum value to the business mission and strategy."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security KRI (Key Risk Indicator)", "Back": "Key Risk Indicator for emerging threats. provides early warning signs and helps organizational management take proactive mitigation actions before risks are realized and cause any significant organizational harm."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Risk Matrix", "Back": "Tool prioritizing vulnerabilities by severity and impact. helps organizational management decide which threats require immediate attention and where to allocate limited security resources effectively and efficiently and accurately."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Compliance GAP Analysis", "Back": "Identifying discrepancies between current posture and standards. provides a roadmap for improvement and ensures that all organizational security efforts align with business goals and mandated protection and privacy requirements."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Internal Security Assessment", "Back": "Evaluation performed by the organization's own team. provides a cost-effective way to monitor compliance and identify gaps before they are discovered during formal and independent external audits."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "External Security Assessment", "Back": "Evaluation by an independent third-party expert. provides unbiased view of organizational security and ensures compliance with legal and regulatory data protection requirements and various industry security standards."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Third-Party Risk Assessment", "Back": "Evaluating security of external partners and vendors. ensures that they meet organizational protection standards and do not introduce new risks into the digital infrastructure and information environment."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Awareness Evaluation", "Back": "Testing workforce knowledge of security risks. aims to reduce human error and foster a culture where every organizational employee protects sensitive and valuable information assets and systems."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Incident Response Simulation", "Back": "Drill mimicking a real-world security breach. used to test the organizational incident response plan and improve the team's preparedness for actual cyber attacks and potential system compromises."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Red Team Assessment", "Back": "Adversarial simulation attempting to breach organizational defenses. provides a realistic test of the overall security posture and the effectiveness of all detective and preventive controls and mechanisms."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Blue Team Defense", "Back": "Personnel responsible for defending organizational systems. they use various tools and procedures to monitor, detect, and respond to cyber threats in real-time and maintain overall protection."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "White Box Security Testing", "Back": "Evaluation where tester has full system knowledge. allows for comprehensive and efficient identification of potential organizational vulnerabilities and coding flaws during systematic assessment and testing activities and processes."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Black Box Security Testing", "Back": "Evaluation where tester has no system knowledge. mimics an external attacker's perspective and provides a realistic measure of organizational security defense effectiveness and resilience against potential cyber threats."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Grey Box Security Testing", "Back": "Evaluation with limited system knowledge. provides a balance between realism and efficiency for measuring organizational system security and identifying potential gaps for remediation and improvement and protection."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Vulnerability Prioritization Strategy", "Back": "Ranking gaps based on their risk level. helps management decide which vulnerabilities to patch first to reduce the overall organizational attack surface and potential exposure to cyber threats."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Vulnerability Remediation", "Back": "Process of fixing identified security weaknesses. includes applying patches and updating configurations to ensure organizational assets and systems remain protected from various evolving cyber threats and attacks."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Remediation Retesting", "Back": "Verifying that fixes have successfully addressed vulnerabilities. ensures that organizational security controls are functioning correctly and that no gaps remain in the overall defense strategy and posture."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Control Benchmark", "Back": "Standard for measuring organizational protection posture. allows for comparison against industry best practices and ensures that security efforts meet all mandated legal and technical protection levels and standards."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Baseline Evaluation", "Back": "Comparing current settings against established security baselines. identifies unauthorized changes and ensures all organizational assets meet the minimum required level of protection from various potential cyber threats."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Digital Forensic Image", "Back": "Bit-by-bit copy of media for investigation. must be captured securely to preserve digital evidence integrity for use in formal organizational audits and legal proceedings and investigations."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Evidence Hashing", "Back": "Generating a unique hash for digital evidence. provides a fingerprint ensuring information has not been altered during the organizational forensic investigation and analysis process and storage activities."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Organizational Security Posture", "Back": "Overall security status of organizational systems and info. includes the effectiveness of technical and administrative controls in protecting assets against various evolving cyber threats and attack methods."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Threat Intel Assessment", "Back": "Using information to understand potential cybersecurity attacks. helps organizations prioritize security assessments based on current trends and known adversary methods and various attack vectors and techniques."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Cyber Risk Management", "Back": "Process identifying, evaluating, and mitigating potential threats. provides the foundation for making informed decisions about organizational security investments and selecting appropriate protective controls and measures and overall strategies."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Compliance Management", "Back": "Process of ensuring adherence to legal and regulatory requirements. essential for avoiding penalties and maintaining trust of customers and various organizational data protection and regulatory authorities and bodies."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Audit Reporting", "Back": "Documenting evaluation findings and recommendations. provides a clear action plan for improvement and objective evidence of organizational compliance for management and various regulatory data bodies and stakeholders."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Vulnerability Management Lifecycle", "Back": "Stages of identifying and fixing security gaps. includes discovery, analysis, prioritization, fixing, and retesting to ensure organizational assets remain constantly protected from various potential cyber threats."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "SOC Monitoring Assessment", "Back": "Evaluation of the central security monitoring team. ensures that organizational personnel have the required tools and training to detect and respond to threats effectively and efficiently and accurately."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Forensic Investigation", "Back": "Capture and study of traffic for investigation. helps organizational security teams understand how a breach occurred and identify indicators of compromise within the network infrastructure and system environment."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "System Hardening Assessment", "Back": "Securing systems by removing unnecessary services and vulnerabilities. a critical corrective action identified during organizational assessments to reduce the overall attack surface area effectively and efficiently and accurately."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Configuration Audit", "Back": "Systematic review of settings for standard compliance. identifies misconfigurations that could be exploited and ensures that organizational security is applied uniformly across all information technology systems and infrastructures."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Network Defense Audit", "Back": "Evaluation of organizational network defense mechanisms. provide objective evidence that all firewalls and IDS/IPS are functioning effectively to protect critical organizational information assets and systems."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Physical Protection Audit", "Back": "Evaluation of protections for personnel and hardware. includes checking locks and cameras to ensure unauthorized individuals cannot reach sensitive organizational areas and critical hardware and servers and facilities."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Personnel Vetting Audit", "Back": "Evaluation of employee vetting and training processes. ensures hiring practices and awareness programs effectively reduce the risk of organizational insider threats and various potential human errors and mistakes."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Data Protection Audit", "Back": "Comprehensive evaluation of the data protection program. ensures technical and administrative controls work together to maintain organizational confidentiality and integrity of all digital and physical information assets and systems."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Evaluation Framework", "Back": "Structured set of guidelines for security assessments. provides consistent and repeatable processes for identifying organizational vulnerabilities and ensuring all mandated data protection and security standards are met effectively."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Threat Source Attribution", "Back": "Process of identifying the specific adversary responsible. helps organizations understand motives and methods, informing the development of targeted and effective organizational defense and protection and risk mitigation strategies."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Indicators of Breach", "Back": "Evidence that a security compromise has occurred. identifying IoCs is a key goal of organizational log analysis and continuous monitoring to detect and respond to threats quickly and accurately."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Attack Vector Identification", "Back": "Determining the path used by an adversary. essential for effective organizational threat modeling and strengthening the defense strategy against potential cyber attacks and unauthorized system access and compromises."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Testing Team", "Back": "Experts responsible for evaluating organizational security. must have the skills and authority to identify vulnerabilities and recommend effective remediation actions for organizational management and all relevant business stakeholders."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Third-party Security Verification", "Back": "Evaluation by a party not involved in design. provides high assurance that organizational security controls are effective and functioning as intended to protect critical information assets and systems."},
        {"Topic": "6", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Assessment and Testing", "Back": "Comprehensive evaluation of organizational defenses. combines various methods to identify vulnerabilities and ensure mandated protection standards are consistently met to maintain a secure and resilient information system environment."},

        # TOPIC 7: SECURITY OPERATIONS (60 Terms)
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Incident Response Strategy", "Back": "Coordinated effort to manage a security breach. Aimed at containing the threat and restoring normal operations while minimizing damage and overall organizational financial loss and operational business impact."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Digital Forensics Investigation", "Back": "Gathering and analyzing electronic evidence after an incident. aims to understand breaches and identify perpetrators while maintaining a strict chain of custody for admissibility in various legal proceedings."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Patch Management Process", "Back": "Strategic process of applying software updates. critical corrective control that closes known vulnerabilities and strengthens the overall security posture of all organizational technology assets and information technology systems."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Vulnerability Management Cycle", "Back": "Cycle of identifying and fixing security gaps. ensures organizational systems remain protected against new threats through regular scanning and effective prioritization of remediation and various mitigation tasks and activities."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Change Management Procedure", "Back": "Formal process for managing system modifications. requires organizational approval to prevent unauthorized changes and reduce the risk of accidental security vulnerabilities or technical operational business disruptions and service failures."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Asset Management Tracking", "Back": "Tracking all hardware and software components. provides visibility into the attack surface and ensures all assets receive required security updates and maintenance across the entire organizational digital and physical environment."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Personnel Security Control", "Back": "Measures ensuring that employees are trustworthy and trained. includes background checks and awareness programs to reduce the risk of organizational insider threats and various human errors and mistakes."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Physical Security Control", "Back": "Protecting tangible assets from physical threats. include locks, cameras, and barriers designed to prevent unauthorized individuals from reaching sensitive organizational areas or critical information technology hardware and infrastructure assets."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "BCP (Business Continuity Planning)", "Back": "Strategy ensuring critical functions survive a disaster. focuses on organizational resilience and the ability to maintain operations during and after a major disruptive event occurs within the business environment."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "DRP (Disaster Recovery Planning)", "Back": "Technical plan for restoring IT systems after failure. includes detailed procedures for recovering data and hardware to minimize operational downtime and overall organizational financial loss and business impact."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "RTO (Recovery Time Objective)", "Back": "The maximum tolerable duration of system downtime. defines how quickly a business function must be restored after a disaster to avoid significant and irreparable harm to the organizational mission."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "RPO (Recovery Point Objective)", "Back": "The maximum tolerable amount of data loss. determines the frequency of backups required to ensure that lost information stays within acceptable limits for organizational recovery and business continuity efforts."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "DLP (Data Loss Prevention) Technology", "Back": "Technical solution that prevents sensitive information from leaving the organization unauthorized. monitors and blocks restricted data in use, in motion, and at rest across all internal organizational systems."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Honeypot Decoy", "Back": "Decoy systems designed to lure and study attackers. provide early organizational threat warning and help security teams understand adversary methods without risking real information assets or critical organizational digital infrastructures."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Sandboxing", "Back": "Isolated environment used to run suspicious code safely. prevents malware from affecting the rest of the organizational system while its behavior is being analyzed by security experts and technical professionals."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "SIEM (Security Information and Event Management)", "Back": "Aggregates and analyzes log data to provide visibility and alerting for potential security incidents and cyber attacks. essential for monitoring the overall organizational security posture and responding quickly to threats."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Security Log Correlation", "Back": "Identifying patterns by linking events from different sources. used to detect sophisticated attacks that bypass individual organizational system security controls and mechanisms by analyzing relationships between different data points."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Egress Traffic Monitoring", "Back": "Evaluating traffic leaving the organizational network. used to detect unauthorized data exfiltration and prevent malware from communicating with its external command and control servers and infrastructure over the public internet."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Incident Response Team Management", "Back": "Group of experts responsible for managing security breaches. includes technical, legal, and management personnel to ensure a coordinated and effective response to various organizational cyber threats and adversary methods."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "SOAR (Security Orchestration, Automation, and Response)", "Back": "Integrated toolset for coordinating security activities. automates repetitive tasks and orchestrates workflows, improving the efficiency and effectiveness of the organizational incident response and defense efforts and defensive strategies."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Investigation Compliance Standard", "Back": "Adhering to legal rules during organizational inquiries. includes evidence handling and reporting to ensure all security assessments and forensic activities meet mandated legal and regulatory data protection and security standards."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Evidence Collection Procedure", "Back": "Gathering digital information after a security incident. requires using specialized organizational tools and techniques to ensure data is captured without alteration and remains admissible in various legal proceedings and court cases."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Evidence Handling Protocol", "Back": "Managing digital artifacts during an investigation. includes secure storage and strict organizational chain of custody documentation to prevent evidence tampering or unauthorized information access by any internal or external third-party."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Investigative Analysis Techniques", "Back": "Scientific methods for analyzing security incidents. aims to understand how breaches occurred and identify adversary actions taken within organizational systems and network infrastructure environments and various critical digital components."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Forensic Investigation Procedure", "Back": "Formal steps for conducting digital investigations. ensure organizational consistency and integrity in evidence gathering, analysis, and reporting to support legal and administrative data protection and security incident response processes."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Artifact Identification Method", "Back": "Finding relevant data from computers and networks. includes identifying malware and user activity traces that provide clues about the specific organizational security incident being formally investigated by the incident response team."},
        {"Topic": "7", "Subtopic": "N/A", "Front": "Logging Activity Monitoring", "Back": "Recording events within organizational information systems. provides a detailed audit trail for monitoring and forensic analysis, ensuring all system and user actions are properly accounted for within the organizational environment."},
